<TEXT>
the soviet union will maintain diplomatic ties 
with iraq for now but still demands that iraq end its occupation of 
kuwait tass reported wednesday following president mikhail 
gorbachevs meeting with the iraqi foreign minister 
us sen bob dole said he believed the minister tareq aziz 
was carrying a message for gorbachev to give to president bush at 
the superpower summit in helsinki 
the kansas republican the minority leader in the senate spoke 
to reporters after his own meeting with the soviet president in the 
kremlin aziz met with gorbachev later in the day 
tass said the meeting was held at the request of iraqi president 
saddam hussein and that the two held a frank discussion on the gulf 
crisis 
it said soviet officials emphasised that they want for the 
moment at least to maintain permanent diplomatic contact with 
iraqi leaders 
until now however no political or diplomatic contacts 
between moscow and baghdad have produced the desired result the 
immediate withdrawal of all iraqi troops from kuwait and the 
restoration of that countrys independence and sovereignty tass 
said 
dole said he thought aziz was coming here hopefully to pass 
some message on to gorbachev that might be passed on to president 
bush 
maybe it will provide some breakthrough maybe some little ray 
of hope maybe saddam hussein now realizes he made a big big 
mistake by invading kuwait on aug 2 dole told an airport news 
conference minutes before leaving for washington 
bush and gorbachev meet in the finnish capital sunday the 
crisis following iraqs invasion of kuwait was expected to rank 
high on their agenda 
aziz was to address a news conference thursday at the soviet 
foreign ministry and was expected to discuss the message he was 
believed to have carried 
dole said he and six other republican senators winding up a trip 
to the soviet union just had a very good visit with president 
gorbachev we talked about a number of issues particularly the 
upcoming summit 
we indicated none of us want armed conflict we hope there 
will be a peaceable solution my impression is that gorbachev 
is in almost total agreement on this point 
he indicated it was a turning point that was very important 
for both countries dole said he sees it as a very important 
meeting when you think about this being the two superpowers 
meeting now for the first time with reference to a conflict where 
they are both on the same side 
gorbachev told the senators his meeting with aziz was 
initiated at the request of the iraqis dole reported he 
said in effect i am prepared to hear them out and of course i 
will be reporting to president bush on what was said and what 
transpired 
in an interview broadcast on soviet television wednesday night 
gorbachev described dole as close to president bush and said 
the conversation was important for me in connection with the 
forthcoming meeting in helsinki 
during the interview gorbachev dwelt almost exclusively with an 
economic program he is expected to announce next week to move the 
soviet union closer to a market economy away from the current 
central planning system 
dole replied when pressed on what proposals gorbachev and bush 
might make to end the gulf crisis i wouldnt even speculate on 
what would transpire 
sen john warner rva said he asked gorbachev to clarify 
this question of the soviets there in the capacity of advisers and 
experts referring to 193 soviet employees affiliated with iraqs 
military 
according to warner gorbachev said right away theyre not 
advisers they have not been involved in the hostilities they are 
simply contractors there to work on the equipment we would like to 
bring them back but if we were to break those contracts and bring 
them back home it could well jeopardize the 60008000 soviets 
there on construction contracts 
warner ranking republican on the senate armed services 
committee said gorbachev also wanted to sign treaties with the 
united states and other western nations to cut conventional and 
longrange nuclear arms by the end of the year 
</TEXT>
