<TEXT>
new york none of the major broadcast tv networks will carry 
live coverage of the liftoff of the space shuttle columbia 
scheduled for 120 am thursday but cable news network plans live 
coverage 
cnn will broadcast the liftoff live and will update its coverage 
throughout the day a spokeswoman said 
an nbc spokeswoman said the network would not itself broadcast 
the space shuttle launch live but would offer a live feed to its 
affiliates to carry if they wish 
representatives of cbs and abc said they had no plans for live 
coverage of the liftoff which is nasas third attempt to send 
columbia on an astronomy mission and its first shuttle flight in 
months 
