considered either a demon or a champion of islam 
some perceive the iraqi president a hero others call him a 
tyrant and fear he will bring disaster to the persian gulf cradle 
of the moslem faith 
nearly twothirds of the worlds estimated 1 billion moslems are 
nonarabs they live in a crescent that reaches from the sands and 
jungles of black africa to the steppes of central asia and juts out 
to islands in the pacific ocean 
the nonarab moslems like their coreligionists in the middle 
east are divided in their opinion of saddam and the presence of 
us troops in the gulf 
some despise him 
some have given him a new name saddma hussein saddma 
means sorrow in the urdu language spoken by many moslems in india 
and pakistan iraqs aug 2 seizure of kuwait has brought misery 
and fears of greater poverty to a halfmillion south asians who 
worked there 
some revere him 
in bangladesh where moslems account for 90 percent of the 110 
million people the government has promised to send 1200 soldiers 
to saudi arabia to guard against further iraqi aggression but at 
least 5500 civilians have volunteered to fight on the iraqi side 
if war breaks out 
i have offered to fight for iraq because president saddam 
hussein is a champion of islamic revivalism said mohammad 
faisal a businessman in dhaka bangladeshs capital 
in predominantly hindu india whose 105 million moslems give it 
the secondlargest moslem population of any country in the world 
the iraqi consul general in bombay has compiled a list of moslem 
volunteers the sunday mail newspaper reported 
we intend to call up these reserves if and when the need 
arises amer naji the consul general said 
in new delhi hundreds of moslems emerging from their weekly 
prayers on friday burned an effigy of president bush to protest the 
american deployment in saudi arabia 
in jakarta capital of indonesia the islamic council for the 
defense of the holy land called a rally to deplore the iraqi 
invasion the 2000 demonstrators also called on the united states 
to withdraw from the gulf indonesia with 162 million moslems is 
the largest moslem country in the world 
the countrys largest moslem organization muhannadiyah has 
urged the americans not to take any arbitrary action 
the us presence is not genuinely aimed at defending the 
interest of an invaded country said yuwono subarsong dean of 
the political faculty of the indonesian university 
he said washington only wants to ensure its oil supply to 
maintain the american way of life 
in pakistan a moslem state with 103 million adherents of the 
religion a poll of 700 people showed 74 percent supported the 
governments decision to send troops to saudi arabia while 11 
percent opposed it but the same poll showed 62 percent opposed the 
presence of american forces in saudi arabia home of the moslem 
worlds most sacred shrines 
in the past two weeks moslem fundamentalists have staged noisy 
but nonviolent antiamerican protests in islamabad karachi and 
other cities 
in india the government avoided direct criticism of saddam and 
thanked him for helping some of the 180000 indian workers in 
kuwait and iraq return home but posters have appeared in the jama 
masjid a new delhi mosque that is one of the worlds largest 
asking iraq to withdraw from kuwait 
in malaysia where 45 percent of the countrys 178 million 
people are moslem the government has backed the united nations 
sanctions against iraq but the opposition pan islamic party held a 
demonstration calling for us withdrawal 
most west african nations with large moslem populations have 
either remained silent or criticized iraq initially and then kept 
quiet 
nigeria africas most populous nation with 119 million people 
half of them moslem has said very little about the invasion but 
it has defied saddams orders to close its embassy in kuwait 
in uganda moslem leaders have criticised hussein 
umar kaggwa a kampala businessman said he thought saddam 
should have learned a lesson from former ugandan leader gen idi 
amin who invaded tanzania and precipitatated his own downfall in 
1978 
i think saddam is mad kaggwa said 
