<TEXT>
president bush has flown the equivalent of 
eight times around the globe in his 20 months as president 
starting this week hell be able to make the circuit without even 
having to stop 
the president who has traveled farther and more frequently than 
any other chief executives at comparable points in their terms 17 
countries and 40 states as president so far will get the ideal 
accompanying piece of hardware a plane capable of staying aloft a 
week or more through midair refueling 
although nearly two years behind schedule the new air force one 
takes flight this week 
bush a former navy pilot is expected to take his maiden flight 
on the new plane a converted jumbo boeing 747 on thursday when 
he gives speeches for republican candidates in topeka kan and 
tallahassee fla 
then he will use it this weekend when he flies to helsinki 
finland for his oneday summit with soviet president mikhail s 
gorbachev 
while midair refueling is an option to be reserved for an 
emergency the new plane can fly 7140 miles without refueling 
thats 1400 miles farther than the present air force one a 
20yearold boeing 707 
it also carries stateoftheart communications systems an 
antimissile system collisionavoidance equipment and is designed 
to protect electronic systems after a nuclear explosion 
the new plane also has 
eightyfive telephones 
twin beds in the presidents stateroom a changing room and a 
shower 
a builtin movie screen and projection systems 
refrigeratorfreezers that can hold a weeks supply of food 
for 70 passengers and 23 crew members 
a private office for the president with eight large chairs and 
a sofa 
seven lavatories 
a medical emergency room 
two copying machines and television videocassette and stereo 
systems 
although the plane originally was intended to be ready for 
