barring any unforeseen complications that would delay use of the 
plane its maiden flight will be a kind of triumphant return to 
kansas its birthplace fitzwater said 
progress on the planes was delayed nearly two years primarily by 
boeings efforts to equip the plane with wiring that could 
withstand a nuclear blast boeing officials have said 
the new plane has about twice as much wiring 126 million feet 
as a commercial 747 
boeing signed a fixedcost contract with the us air force to 
deliver both planes for 250 million although the price later was 
revised to about 266 million actual costs rose to close to 400 
million air force officials have said with much of the overrun 
being absorbed by boeing 
the larger planes also required construction of a new hangar at 
andrews air force base in the maryland suburbs of washington 
the designation air force one does not relate to a specific 
plane but rather to whatever plane the president is riding on 
when he takes a small gulfstream as he sometimes does on the way 
to camp david md that becomes air force one 
the first air force one was a fourengine pistonpowered 
dc4 flown by franklin roosevelt in 1942 and dubbed sacred cow 
the new 747 will replace the current 707 air force no 2700 
that is primarily used as air force one 
the second plane will replace the backup 707 now used for 
presidential travel air force no 2600 on which lyndon johnson 
took the oath of office on nov 22 1963 
that plane which bush uses occasionally is the first jet ever 
used by a president 
