<TEXT>
police fatally shot six students 
protesting plans to give more jobs to lowcaste hindus and growing 
violence prompted the government today to cancel bus service 
linking new delhi with state capitals 
the buses were canceled to avoid clashes and attacks on 
stateowned buses during a 50hour strike beginning thursday that 
students have called 
they are protesting prime minister vp singhs proposal to 
reserve half of all government jobs for lower castes 
thousands of passengers were stranded at new delhis inter state 
bus terminus today at least 25000 people a day normally travel on 
buses from the station the largest in india 
said a transport official at the bus terminal we are running 
only those limited services which can return to the depot by this 
evening 
police in bihar indias poorest state opened fire on students 
tuesday killing at least six people and wounding 50 news reports 
said the violence raises to 14 the number of people killed in four 
weeks of street protests against singhs decision 
the statesman newspaper said students had set numerous cars on 
fire and attempted to storm the government secretariat in patna 
the capital of the eastern state of bihar 
indian express a new delhibased newspaper said groups of 
students planned to block all traffic on the streets of the capital 
when the strike begins thursday 
an organization of uppercaste farmers that commands wide 
support in areas around new delhi has pledged support and said its 
members will block all roads leading to the city 
prime minister singh announced aug 7 that 49 percent of 
government jobs would be reserved on the basis of caste up from a 
previous 22 percent in addition 5 to 10 percent of jobs would be 
reserved for poor people regardless of caste and the rest would be 
awarded on merit he said 
the proposal raised a storm of protest the government employs 
18 million people and a whitecollar job is muchsought by 
graduating students 
opponents said singh was attempting to buy votes from the lower 
castes who form a majority of indias 880 million people 
the chief opposition party the congress party of previous prime 
minister rajiv gandhi has dismissed the proposals as politically 
motivated 
media criticism has also been fierce the biweekly india today 
magazine said tuesday that the decision marked the descent of 
singh from leader to demagogue 
he has been reduced to a votehungry power broker 
shamelessly using the two elements which have ever bloodied and 
divided this nation religion and caste the news magazine said 
hindus who make up 82 percent of the countrys people are 
divided into four main castes and hundreds of subcastes 
discrimination on the basis of caste is legally banned but in 
reality the system permeates much of indian life especially in 
rural areas 
