aug 29 
the record hackensack nj on opening the raoul wallenberg 
files 
raoul wallenberg a swedish diplomat saved the lives of as many 
as 100000 jews in hungary during the closing months of world war 
ii then wallenberg vanished an apparent victim of bloodthirsty 
soviet secret police who suspected he was a spy 
but reports that wallenberg may have survived into the 1980s 
and still may even be alive have intrigued investigators of the 
stature of the late andrei sakharov now the soviet union in one 
of the most dramatic acts of glasnost has agreed to open its files 
on wallenberg 
soviet officials now say that they will open the archives of the 
kgb and other agencies to an international commission investigating 
the fate of wallenberg it is almost certainly too late to save 
wallenberg as he saved so many others but at least the world can 
learn the truth about his fate by refusing to give up their quest 
for the truth investigators have honored one of the centurys 
authentic heroes 
