sept 4 
philadelphia inquirer on the ussoviet summit 
with each passing month it becomes increasingly clear that the 
soviet union is no longer americas chief adversary in the world 
indeed it is coming to look more and more like an ally the sept 
9 ussoviet summits main purpose is to intensify international 
pressure on iraqs saddam hussein a venture in which the united 
states and soviet union are on the same side 
the united states and the soviet union still have thousands of 
nuclear warheads trained on each others territory and 
negotiations aimed at reducing those weapons have stalled but 
weve reached a stage where the specter of deadlocked arms talks no 
longer arouses a sense of foreboding 
that could change of course in the unlikely event that soviet 
president mikhail gorbachev is ousted in favor of someone more 
menacing but for now a bushgorbachev meeting reminds one less 
of the superpower summits of old than of those routine 
gettogethers a us president has from time to time with the west 
german chancellor or the british prime minister 
