sept 1 
the kansas city star on the persian gulf 
as the us and its allies face mounting costs in the persian 
gulf and the possibility of a long standoff some tempers are 
getting short over what different countries should contribute to 
the effort 
americans are complaining that other countries arent doing as 
much as they should japanese officials are grousing that they 
arent cashdispensing machines western european politicians are 
waffling over what their nations responsibilities are 
it should be remembered that absolute justice and precision are 
impossible burdensharing debates are hard enough at the platoon 
level where countries are concerned allies must weigh factors 
that include size interests wealth history military 
preparedness and other commitments 
the us has the military power to make the world a little safer 
in situations like the current crisis there is no getting around 
the fact however that exercising that power sometimes entails 
fiscal as well as substantial human costs the fiscal costs can be 
better shared 
