sept 2 
sunday mail harare zimbabwe on the persian gulf 
once western economies wobble the ripple effects reach 
developing countries sooner rather than later and the effect 
of the crisis in the persian gulf will be felt when many 
developing countries are perhaps most vulnerable 
many have adopted exportled structural adjustment programs and 
if a recession however mild is added to the growing trend in 
trade protectionism in the west those programs could stumble and 
fall 
this once again highlights the importance of developing 
countries to lessen their present almost total reliance on western 
markets for both exports and imports 
aug 30 
the statesman calcutta india on the persian gulf 
