<TEXT>
the chairman of the house banking committee on 
wednesday proposed limiting the number of accounts that can be 
insured by the government and perhaps reducing maximum coverage 
below 100000 
deposit insurance is at the heart of our financial and 
economic stability said rep henry gonzalez dtexas we 
ignore its problems only with the greatest peril 
gonzalez in a speech to the house noted that in the wake of 
the failure of the fund that insured deposits in savings and loan 
institutions the bank insurance fund is facing a fifth straight 
year of multibilliondollar losses 
despite doubling bank insurance deposit premiums it will take 
as long as five years for the fund to reach a reasonably safe 
level he said 
key elements of the plan proposed by gonzalez would 
limit the number of accounts protected by federal insurance and 
consider reducing the 100000 maximum insurance 
under present law about 99 percent of all deposits are insured 
because a wealthy person can use joint and trust accounts to avoid 
the 100000 limit gonzalez said the changes also would prevent 
abuse of the insurance by pension and other investment funds 
allow regulators to raise assessments for insurance premiums as 
the need arises institutions that engage in greater risks would 
have to pay more for deposit insurance 
toughen capitalization requirements so bank owners would have 
more of their own money at risk 
limit permissible investments for insured deposits 
require a parent holding company to share responsibility for 
losses incurred by any insured affiliate 
the 1989 law bailing out depositors in failed sampls created one 
fund to insure bank deposits which already is in operation and a 
second to insure sampl deposits starting in 1992 
although the law requires the bank fund to have a reserve of at 
least 125 for each 100 of covered deposits huge losses have 
reduced the actual reserve ratio to about 60 cents per 100 
gonzalez said 
