violation of the un embargo a navy spokesman said the ship was 
allowed to proceed to an unspecified port after a 30hour search 
though hundreds of westerners were allowed to leave baghdad 
tuesday and today iraqi red tape kept many others waiting despite 
iraqi promises to expedite departures british officials said iraq 
had intercepted 30 british women and children trying to join a 
convoy leaving kuwait 
jordans king hussein traveled to baghdad to try to keep 
diplomatic efforts alive he was to hold talks with saddam today or 
thursday 
in moscow iraqi foreign minister tariq aziz met soviet leader 
mikhail s gorbachev to discuss the gulf crisis 
the trip came a day after soviet foreign minister eduard a 
shevardnadze proposed an international conference on the persian 
gulf crisis president bush and gorbachev are to hold a summit 
sunday in helsinki finland 
in other diplomatic efforts secretary of state james a baker 
iii was headed today for the middle east west germany and italy 
treasury secretary nicholas brady met in london with prime minister 
margaret thatcher 
mrs thatcher promised to contribute to a usorganized fund to 
help nations worst hit by unordered sanctions on iraq british 
officials said a thatcher spokeswoman speaking on condition of 
anonymity reported the prime minister said the united kingdom 
would certainly contribute and would let the united states have 
detailed figures as soon as possible 
brady and baker are also seeking financial commitments to help 
ease the burden of maintaining a us expeditionary force in saudi 
arabia as part of the international effort to pressure saddam into 
withdrawing from kuwait 
baker said tuesday that the bush administration envisions 
maintaining a military presence in the persian gulf even if iraq 
leaves oilrich kuwait which it invaded aug 2 he said the united 
states is considering creating a natotype alliance to deal with 
future security threats in the region 
meanwhile the airlift of westerners from iraq mostly women and 
children continued today 
seven british and four american women arrived in amman on the 
regular morning iraqi airways flight from baghdad and a 
frenchchartered iraqi airways jetliner also arrived in amman with 
105 western women and children including 10 americans 
in addition a virgin atlantic airways flight with 25 us 
hostages from baghdad was headed for newark nj later this 
afternoon the americans traveled via amman and london 
the iraqi news agency today quoted an unidentified government 
spokesman as saying iraq was doing its best to speed the departure 
of foreign women and children 
iraq endeavors with all possible means to ensure their 
departure in cooperation with concerned countries the news 
agency reported it said all border points were open for their 
departure and the iraqi airways was ready to lease its aircraft 
for flying them to any capital 
iraq had slowed the release process by denying foreign jets 
landing rights and by forcing westerners to deal with visa red tape 
saddam has said women and children can leave but foreign men 
are being kept behind as human shields against any us attack on 
strategic sites 
in baghdad 306 british women and children who arrived in a 
sevenbus convoy from kuwait on tuesday night were awaiting exit 
visas today diplomats said on condition of anonymity the group 
was expected to leave baghdad on thursday or friday 
however iraqis intercepted 30 british women and children trying 
to join the convoy tuesday as it left kuwait the foreign office 
said today they were being detained in a hotel the officials 
said they gave no further details 
about 11000 westerners were believed still stranded in kuwait 
and iraq 
in addition tens of thousands of asian refugees are stranded in 
jordan with no way to get home many have gathered in desert camps 
where food and water are scarce and sanitary facilities almost 
nonexistent 
on tuesday at one of the camps thousands of refugees pushed and 
scuffled next to a truck from which jordanian officials distributed 
rations a round piece of flat arab bread one tomato and one 
small cucumber per person 
jordanian soldiers on duty stripped off their belts and started 
flailing the ragged refugees yelling at them to stop fighting and 
get into line 
at a news conference in amman jordans crown prince hassan 
criticized the lack of attention given to the refugees and appealed 
for help international relief organizations also called for more 
aid 
most of the more than 100000 refugees stranded in jordan are 
from bangladesh india pakistan sri lanka the philippines and 
thailand 
baker testifying tuesday before the house foreign affairs 
committee discussed ways the united states might confront future 
security challenges in the persian gulf and suggested an alliance 
like the north atlantic treaty organization 
i think we will have to give consideration to working with 
others to create a new security structure for the region baker 
said i think thats likely to be required even if there is a 
pullback by iraq from kuwait 
the white house announced tuesday that bush had decided to ask 
congress to forgive egypts entire 7 billion military debt in 
appreciation for president hosni mubaraks role in standing up to 
iraqi aggression 
