<TEXT>
american women who are part of the military 
buildup in saudi arabia may have to get used to cultural 
differences that put them in a subservient role the white house 
said wednesday 
it is something our military is grappling with said white 
house spokesman marlin fitzwater describing it as just one of 
many similar kinds of cultural situations that our service men and 
women are running into there 
the saudi expect female soldiers to conform to such cultural 
practices as not allowing women to shop alone the culture bars 
socializing or having personal contact even for business with a 
member of the opposite sex who is not a relative 
the pentagon did get a special exemption from the saudi 
government to allow women to drive trucks forklifts and other 
vital equipment saudi women are not allowed to drive 
when shopping female soldiers must be accompanied by a male who 
makes the purchases while the woman stands with her eyes downcast 
to avoid offending the male shopkeeper 
we are working on it fitzwater said when asked whether the 
administration was trying to remedy the situation our commanders 
are working with the saudis and trying to develop new programs and 
processes for living there that can accommodate both cultures 
