<TEXT>
a scandal dubbed israels watergate eclipsed 
news of the persian gulf crisis here wednesday featuring 
accusations of highlevel political fraud and questions on the 
propriety of wiretapping under jewish law 
it rattled nerves in prime minister yitzhak shamirs 
narrowbased coalition cabinet and renewed tension between israels 
two main communities sephardic jews from africa and the middle 
east and ashkanazim of european origin 
national police commissioner yaacov turner under fire for 
investigating interior minister ariyeh deri defended himself 
against charges by deris supporters that the probe began because 
deri is a sephardic jew born in morocco 
its crazy turner said to prevent an investigation they 
are willing to break up an entire people whoever helps this along 
is worse than a criminal 
police minister roni milo of prime minister yitzhak shamirs 
likud bloc said he will summon turner on thursday to discuss that 
comment 
