said turners comments dealt with issues not related to 
proper functioning of the police force and its national tasks 
the scandal began last week with reports that five people were 
held on suspicion of bugging the telephone of investigative 
reporter mordechai gilat of the newspaper yediot ahronot 
a recorder was found on a motorcycle outside gilats home with 
wires running through his phone box and into his tel aviv apartment 
gilat wrote articles in june that led to police investigation of 
deri 31 a leading member of the ultraorthodox torah guardians 
party known by the hebrew acronym shas deri is suspected of 
misappropriating millions of shekels in government money by 
diverting funds from local councils to religious institutions after 
taking office in december 1988 
a shekel is worth just over 50 cents 
