<TEXT>
czechoslovakian leader alexander dubcek 
feasted on sausages and potato dumplings wednesday and told 
residents of a town founded by czech immigrants they were like 
members of my family 
i am glad that many of you have found a new mother country in 
the united states the president of the czechoslovakian 
