southern minnesota farming community 
children chanted dubcek dubcek and waved czechoslovakian 
and american flags 
i am especially glad that the new generation that is here does 
not forget the old country he said through a translator 
in an effort to inject life into czechoslovakias sagging 
economy a sixmember delegation including top ministers of 
industry and science is visiting minnesota to learn about medical 
and computer technology 
soviet president mikhail s gorbachev made a oneday visit to 
the state in june for similar reasons 
dubcek met with about 100 health care executives tuesday at 
medtronic inc the worlds largest maker of cardiac pacemakers in 
the minneapolis suburb of fridley 
dubcek said at a luncheon address wednesday that the shift from 
a planned economy to a free market system will progress slowly and 
painfully over several years 
destruction of the totalitarian power is not enough he 
said it is necessary to rebuild the economic structure from 
scratch we want to avoid the danger of excess inflation that has 
so badly hit our neighbors in poland and hungary 
that can be spurred by foreign investment and joint ventures 
with american entrepreneurs the czechoslovakian leader said 
our industry is considerably sound even if some of our 
industrial branches may be obsolete he said we have qualified 
workers and technicians who are experienced we have a relatively 
low foreign debt 
earlier dubcek joined local and state officials for breakfast 
at schumachers new prague hotel they ate the czech sausage 
jiternice with horseradish along with biscuits potato dumplings 
and scrambled eggs 
dubcek now 68 was led the 1968 prague spring liberalization 
movement that was crushed by warsaw pact forces last year he 
regained his post as head of parliament following two decades of 
political exile and relative obscurity 
he told a crowd gathered on the steps of the st wenceslaus 
