<TEXT>
ibm today announced its next 
generation of mainframe computers as part of a strategy designed to 
ensure the large machines place at the center of corporate 
information systems 
the worlds largest computer company also announced replacement 
models for several lowerlevel computer lines in what the company 
said was its most sweeping announcement in 25 years 
international business machines corp announced 18 new 
computers including a topoftheline model that provides twice 
the power of its current highend model 
the new machines are part of what ibm calls its system390 line 
replacing its current system370 this is only the third mainframe 
system line from ibm since the early 1960s 
the new machines which are called the enterprise system9000 
family range in price from 70480 to 228 million 
ibm says its new topend model will be the most powerful 
computer on the market however this model wont be available 
until the third quarter of 1991 many of the lower level models 
will be available later this year or early next year 
as part of its announcement today ibm also disclosed new ways 
to link various size computers in a network and new operating 
system software for the new computer line 
despite the increasing popularity of smaller computers 
mainframes account for about half of ibms profits when associated 
software and equipment are included that makes acceptance of the 
new models crucial 
the introduction of the new machines which has been rumored for 
more than a year also is important to ibm because its competitors 
are stepping up the pressure 
the major makers of ibmcompatible mainframes hitachi data 
systems corp fujitsu and amdahl corp all are planning major 
upgrades to their machines 
on tuesday fujitsu japans largest computer maker beat ibm to 
the punch it announced a powerful new mainframe that it says is 
the fastest in the world fujitsu officials said the top model in 
their new m1800 series is capable of executing up to 600 million 
instructions per second or mips in scientific calculations 
however the fujitsu machine would not be capable of achieving that 
speed in commercial applications 
analysts say the new topoftheline ibm computer will run at a 
maximum speed of about 230 mips ibms current mostpowerful 
mainframe can handle about 112 mips ibm does not disclose its mips 
ratings of computers 
ibm also said that customers will be able to link eight of the 
next topend models to operate as one machine boosting power 
dramatically 
fujitsus new technology is likely to appear in mainframes 
produced by amdahl a us maker of ibmcompatible mainfames that 
is 45 percent owned by fujitsu 
hitachi and amdahl traditionally undercut ibms prices and 
their share of the us mainframe market has been growing while 
ibms slipped in recent years but ibm still holds about 87 percent 
of the us highend mainframe market according to computer 
intelligence a la jolla calif research firm 
ibm compared the importance of todays announcement to the 1964 
disclosure of its system360 line considered a milestone in the 
computer industry 
the company even rented a special amtrak train to take reporters 
from new york city to the announcement site at its poughkeepsie 
mainframe plant 
mainframes typically are used by large corporations such as 
airlines and insurance companies to hold vast amounts of data such 
as information on millions of customer accounts 
the new ibm machines feature fiberoptic lines to link the 
computers to datastorage devices fiberoptic lines which 
transmit information in beams of laser light can move data to the 
computers processor at about twice the rate of the standard 
electrical lines used on the 3090s ibms current top machines 
helping speed processing 
while the system390 represents a major improvement some 
analysts say it doesnt appear to be the breakthrough they earlier 
expected 
it is not a qualitatively different type of technology the 
3090 is being extended said tom willmott a vice president of 
aberdeen group a bostonbased research firm 
he doesnt think the doubling of processing power will do much 
to improve the operation of database programs that are among the 
most popular uses for highend mainframes 
analysts also expressed concern that some of the new models 
wont be available until the second half of 1991 that lag could 
cause customers to defect to competitiors or postpone orders that 
would have gone to 3090s hurting ibms revenues 
