xerox corp on wednesday began offering a 
total satisfaction guarantee that promises a free replacement 
to customers dissatisfied with any of the companys products 
the guarantee covers all xerox products delivered from now on 
for three years or for the full term of financing through xerox 
whichever is longer 
a customer not totally satisfied with a product for whatever 
reason can have it replaced with the same or comparable product 
entirely at xerox expense company officials said at a news 
conference 
we believe this is clearly different from anything thats out 
there today said paul v cahn vice president of reprographics 
and customer service marketing 
the customer is the sole arbiter and decisionmaker with 
virtually every other guarantee or warranty the company decides 
whether a replacement is needed 
david schofield an industry analyst with duff amp phelps in 
chicago said the guarantee might help ease a little buyer 
fear and is probably more psychological than anything else 
i dont know that its going to be a huge boost to sales he 
said i agree with them that it probably wont cost a whole lot 
either 
james j miller xeroxs manager of reprographic product 
marketing said the company does not expect the guarantee to be a 
major expense 
we dont think that were going to get a lot of machines 
back he said 
for the past two years xerox has offered threeyear warranties 
covering repairs on most of its lowvolume consumer products under 
those warranties the company decided whether or not to replace a 
machine cahn said 
the new guarantee supplements existing warranties and applies to 
machines bought rented or leased from xerox or an authorized 
dealer customers must have a xerox service contract 
cahn said xerox expects the guarantee to increase sales in all 
areas the pledge will be extensively advertised over the next few 
weeks he said 
