announced plans to develop an electronic system with reuters 
holdings plc for trading securities in the 170 billion private 
placement market 
the announcement follows a recent rule change by the securities 
and exchange commission making it easier for securities firms to 
sell unregistered stocks and bonds to big institutions 
amex said the new electronic marketplace for trading the 
securities is expected to be implemented in the first half of 1991 
and will be called the system for institutional trading of 
unregistered securities of situs 
amex chairman james r jones said in a statement the new system 
would help companies from any country to gain access to a rich 
and largely untapped source of capital liquidity 
the secs new rule 144a exempts us and foreign institutions 
from registration requirements for the sale of stocks and bonds to 
big institutions the market is used largely to sell corporate debt 
the rule was expected to give a boost to the securities industry 
during a slump in trading of stocks and bonds on the public market 
and other business areas but activity there has slumped as well 
us private placement financings fell by one third in the first 
half of 1990 to 553 billion from 821 billion a year earlier 
idd information services said tuesday 
the drop occurred despite the sec rule change and a drying up in 
the junk bond market as a source for corporate financing idd said 
under the agreement for private placement electronic trading 
situs owuld be a division or subsidiary of the exchange 
