lower us interest rates 
gold prices moved higher in most world trading centers 
heavy dollar selling began in asia and carried over into later 
european and us dealing 
the sales were triggered by speculation that the federal reserve 
soon might seek to foster a us economic rebound by pushing 
interest rates down falling us rates would reduce returns on 
dollar holdings and lessen investment interest in dollars 
currency dealers said the dollar also was hampered by 
speculation that west germany and japan soon may raise their 
interest rates higher rates in those countries especially if us 
rates go down would tend to spur demand for marks and yen 
