<TEXT>
the dollar approached its lowest opening level in 
almost a year against the japanese yen thursday while share prices 
on the tokyo stock exchange inched up 
the dollar opened at 14148 yen down 082 yen from its 
wednesday close the dollar was quoted at 14165 yen late during 
new yorks wednesday session 
the dollar opened at 14097 yen on oct 19 1989 
a trader with fuji bank who spoke on condition of anonymity 
said the lower opening was in part due to a rumor that life 
insurance companies had sold dollars in sydney prior to the 
opening of the tokyo market 
buy orders for the dollar appeared on the tokyo market shortly 
after it opened he said 
dealers are adjusting positions ahead of possible credit 
easing by the us federal reserve and employment statistics due 
to come out friday he said 
many economists say the us economy is headed into a recession 
and the fed will move to lower interest rates to spark economic 
activity 
lower interest rates tend to make a nations currency less 
attractive to foreign investors 
in stock trading the closely watched nikkei stock average of 
225 selected issues rose 3230 points or 013 percent in the 
first 30 minutes of trading on wednesday the index fell 82930 
points 
the price of the benchmark no 119 10year japanese government 
bond declined to 8262 points from 8276 wednesday its yield was 
8210 percent up from 8180 percent 
